				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I'm doing some pixel art and I'd like to know if there's a technical limitation holding back smooth animation on NES hardware. Seems like most games use very few frames for running. I was able to dramatically improve Contra's run animation by going from 3 unique leg positions to 5.<br /><br />Is it possible to delay each frame individually by a different amount? In photoshop, I'm able to specify a delay in fractions of a second. And I can also give some frames more delay than others. Can the NES do this?<br /><br />Lastly, has anyone made a demo showing a heavy frame running animation like that in Super Metroid?</div>

