					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">FitzRoy wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Lastly, has anyone made a demo showing a heavy frame running animation like that in Super Metroid?</div><br />My Indivisible has an 8 frame run: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://kasumi.itch.io/indivisible">https://kasumi.itch.io/indivisible</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Attached is some 3rd Strike animation in an NES ROM.<br /><div class="attachtitle">Attachment:</div><div class="attachcontent">
			<span class="genmed">
				<img src="./styles/subsilver2/imageset/icon_topic_attach.gif" width="14" height="18" alt="" title="" /> 
				<a href="./download/file.php?id=12986">3rdStrikeChun.nes</a> [384.02 KiB]
			</span><br />
			<span class="gensmall">Downloaded 26 times</span>
		

		<br />
	</div><br />A changes the animation. While I didn't change the timing per frame for this, it's certainly possible. <br />Edit: Just because it's easy for me to do, here's specifically Samus' run from Super Metroid.  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=":wink:" title="Wink" /> <br /><div class="attachtitle">Attachment:</div><div class="attachcontent">
			<span class="genmed">
				<img src="./styles/subsilver2/imageset/icon_topic_attach.gif" width="14" height="18" alt="" title="" /> 
				<a href="./download/file.php?id=12988">SamusRun.nes</a> [40.02 KiB]
			</span><br />
			<span class="gensmall">Downloaded 27 times</span>
		

		<br />
	</div><br /><br />These ROMs were made in the <a href="https://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?f=21&amp;t=17082&amp;start=0" class="postlink">unreleased build of my I-CHR software</a> that rainwarrior mentioned. There are holes in Chun Li's body because most of the frames use more than 63 sprites. (NES can draw 64 sprites, I-CHR only supports 63 in a single character frame to avoid moving a pointer)<br /><br />Here's the workflow:<br /><img src="https://i.imgur.com/fCyZuar.gif" alt="Image" /><br />Not shown, but this program does guess palettes and make tiles even if the sprite is &gt;3 colors. (Like Indivisible's Ajna.) You basically import a PNG sequence and it does the rest.<br />Everyone else did a good job explaining why many games probably avoided doing animation like this, so I won't cover it again.<br /><br />I hope to make it easier to do with I-CHR, but it seems like the version of the program that handles sprite animation will never actually come out.</div>

					
