				</span>

			</td>
			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Welcome to what romhacking is all about, and why it's a kind of art, driven by passion and dedication.  And why, in almost all circumstances, you need an assembly programmer to disassemble + reverse-engineer the game to figure out a) where there's free space (if any; and if not, double the ROM size and write code to make use of the new space), b) figure out how all the existing code works, and c) make relevant code changes so that said new graphics can get utilised correctly.  Full-fledged romhacks of this sort are very complicated and time-consuming. That is why you don't see more of them.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

